The paper discusses the development of a microscopic traffic simulator using a Deep Reinforcement Learning Algorithm based on a combination of visual frames and a vector of numerical parameters. This involves the use of AI and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the cs.AI and cs.LG sub-categories. The paper also focuses on multi-agent scenarios, which suggests that it may be relevant to the cs.MA sub-category. Additionally, the use of visual frames implies that the paper may be relevant to the cs.CV sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the simulation of driving styles, which may be relevant to the cs.RO sub-category.
